<p>The plant extracts (dissolved in 10% (
 <italic>v</italic>/
 <italic>v</italic>) DMSO) were diluted in insulin-containing medium and added to the cells on Day 4. Then, the plant extracts were diluted in basic medium and added to the cells again on Day 6, followed by 3 days of incubation. The lipid content of the adipocytes was measured using AdipoRed™ reagent (LONZA, Tokyo, Japan). 
 <italic>Brucea javanica</italic> extract (0.05 mg/mL), which is known to reduce lipid accumulation, was used as the positive control [
 <xref rid="B20-pharmaceuticals-13-00056" ref-type="bibr">20</xref>], and 0.1% DMSO was used as the negative control. The experiments were repeated at least twice (
 <italic>n</italic> = 8 each), and representative values (mean ± SD) are presented in the figures and tables. Lipid accumulation reduction activity (% decrease relative to control) was calculated as follows:
